# dbt Secondary Repo Sync

dbt Cloud reads from `responsum-team/dbtproject`, NOT from `elixirrjob1/cursorskills`.
Pushing to main is not enough — you must also sync to the secondary repo or dbt Cloud will run old code.

## When to sync

After any commit that touches `dbt_project/drip_transformations/` — models, macros, schema YAML, sources.

## How to sync (correct method — no force push)

Clone the secondary repo, overwrite its contents with the dbt project files, and push normally. Never force push.

```bash
source .env   # loads PAT2

rm -rf /tmp/dbt-sync-target
git clone "https://${PAT2}@github.com/responsum-team/dbtproject.git" /tmp/dbt-sync-target
rsync -av --delete --exclude='.git' \
  /home/fillip/projec/cursorskills/dbt_project/drip_transformations/ \
  /tmp/dbt-sync-target/
cd /tmp/dbt-sync-target
git add -A
git diff --cached --quiet || git commit -m "sync: update from elixirrjob1/cursorskills main"
git push
```

After syncing, verify `dbt_project.yml` is at root of the secondary repo — if not, dbt Cloud will error with "valid dbt project was not found".

## Common mistakes

- Using `git push --force` to responsum-team/dbtproject — forbidden, always use the rsync + normal push above.
- Running `git filter-repo` on the main repo — it removes the `origin` remote and destroys local history.
- Using `scripts/push-dbt-remote.sh` — it attempts a merge pull which causes conflicts. Use the rsync method above instead.
- Triggering a dbt Cloud job immediately after pushing to `elixirrjob1/cursorskills` without syncing — the job will run against old code.

## Hash key consistency rule

All FK hashes in fact views must use the same formula as their target dim PK hashes.

DimCustomer and DimProduct PKs are computed as:
```sql
HASH(CAST(id AS VARCHAR) || '|' || 'ERP')
```

FactSales FKs must match:
```sql
HASH(COALESCE(CAST(CUSTOMER_ID AS VARCHAR), '#@#@#@#@#') || '|' || 'ERP') AS "CustomerHashFK"
HASH(COALESCE(CAST(PRODUCT_ID AS VARCHAR), '#@#@#@#@#') || '|' || 'ERP') AS "ProductHashFK"
```

If a FK mismatch is reported, check the hash formula in both the fact view and the dim view before triggering a reload.
